an class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 3:29:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapon Question</span><hr size=1> A weapon with a heal proc is always beneficial to the group because it saves cleric mana.. So IMO use it. Where does this weapon come from anyway?<br><br>Parser Link<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://kqp.mpog.com/EQParse/">kqp.mpog.com/EQParse/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br><br> <p><p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1840"> <img src="http://www.mindspring.com/~johnduke/knosos2.jpg" </a> <p><a href="http://www.lotuscult.com"> Lotus Cult </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 3:49:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapon Question</span><hr size=1> If you're the only tank, deal damage.<br><br>If you're on a raid or in some other large force (or tank-heavy force), then use the Jeldorin. <p>Angelsyn Whitewings, Cleric of Tunare for 40 Seasons.<BR>Tailor (Not really.) - 26<BR>Fletcher (For about half an hour) - 51<BR>Jeweler (Kinda gave up on it.) - 76<BR>Mistress Brewer (ya!  Thank you Aurroean Knights!) - 154<BR>Mistress Baker (Making cakes now.) - 143<BR>Mistress Smith (No more Banded!) - 192<BR>Mistress Fisherwoman (in my spare time.) - 149<BR>Mistress Potter (Done with Cookie cutters.) - 102<BR><BR>Keyne Falconer, Paladin of Erollisi Marr for 43 Seasons.<BR>Baker (Sometimes.) - 75<BR>Brewer (Yeah right.) - 18<BR>Smith (For Screaming Steel) - 21<BR>Tailor (Very slowly.) - 87<BR><BR>Saroyah, Shamaness of the Vah Shir for 13 Seasons. ;)<BR>Tailoring - 23<BR>Fletching - 37<BR>Pottery - 55<BR>Brewing - 56<BR>Smithing - 35<BR>Baking - 24<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utigerheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigerheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 4:31:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapon Question</span><hr size=1>   Aye stick to the Jeldorin. The DPS on it is Close enough compared to the 30 35 weapon. I think its 16.50 for Jeldron and 17.25 for  the 30 35 weapon. So you not missing out on that much Dmg. the 162 point heal is Good as the 35Ac from your shield. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=152485">Tigerheart</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umrbone1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MrBone1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 7:23:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapon Question</span><hr size=1> Jeldorin is one of the best weapons until you need to concentrate on hard damage.  It's heal allows you to fight longer and gain experiance faster.  Also saves the cleric mana which in the end speeds up experiance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubeldukil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beldukil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 3738<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 8:30:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapon Question</span><hr size=1> I disagree. On a raid you want to do as much damage as possible so use 2h.<br><br>If you are in a grgoup you MIGHT use Jeldorin if you have a ton of damage dealers and you wont be doing much damage anyway and you are the main tank. <p><center><imgsrc="http://beld.freeservers.com/images/beld.jpg"> <br><table border=0>  <tr><td><imgsrc="http://www.wise.k12.va.us/cms/images/animatedKnightLeft.gif">    </td><td>Beldukil Lawbringer<br> Level 60 Crusader of Tunare<br>Innit<br>Xev<br>    </td><td><img src="http://www.wise.k12.va.us/cms/images/animatedKnightLeft.gif"></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aryllyian>Aryllyian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 10:00:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapon Question</span><hr size=1> Ayep, I agree with Beld....<br><br>In a raid situation, Paladins use the BIG 2handers to do as much damage as possible while some Fattie Warrior takes the damage and needs the heals.<br><br>Unless you are MA, use the 2hs....<br><br>If you are MA use shield and 1hs....for many of the reasons listed above.<br><br><br>Aryllyian<br>Knight 55<br>Elven Elite, Morrel Thule<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 363<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 11:00:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapon Question</span><hr size=1> I would personally hold on to the jeldorin since it is a weapon that can come in quite useful during aoe encounters when you are all short on healers.<br><br>The sword almost heals up all damage you get from aoe during a ToV fight/farm, so at times when the choice is between you dying or dealing a little less damage and living, then the jeldorin has a good place.<br><br>The weapon is rather seldom for sale on the market. <br><br>For general fighting/soloing/tanking I would use the 2h first and when healing becomes an issue switch to jeldorin some. You really need to parse 2h and jeldorin out to see how much healing you receive from the procs versus the added damage you deal. <br><br>From group to group the weapon that is better to use might change. When you are in group without enough healing but lots of damage output then obviously the reduced damage from jeldorin will be highly compensated by the reduced damage you take as a tank and the free healing you receive. E.g. 5 meeles in the group. You will only contribute 1/5 of the damage on average. Therefore reducing your damage by 30% will not matter too much, but waiting for you to helm heal will =p <p>Senchy Solariatus <BR>60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife<BR>56 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)<BR>Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>Typical Raid Setup</a><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66884>AC Solo Gear</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=362.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=362.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=7><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.emailToFriend?topicID=362.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.threadControl?topicID=362.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=362.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=362.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpaddi